                <section id="hundertwasserexperience">
                    <h2>Hundertwasser Experience</h2>
                    <!--<figure><picture><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemici/hundertwasserexperience.png" media="(max-width: 700px)"/><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemedii/hundertwasserexperience.png" media="(max-width: 1200px)"><img src="resurse/images/hundertwasserexperience.png" alt="Hundertwasser Experience" title="Hundertwasser Experience"/></picture><figcaption>Hundertwasser Experience, Leipzig</figcaption></figure>-->
                    <p>Hello again my dear friend! Yesterday I had the great pleasure to visit for the first time an immersive art show at Leipzig. 
                        The Hundertwasser experience takes you into the world of the Austrian painter, designer and architect Friedensreich Hundertwasser (1928-2000) 
                        with an explosion of colors and overwhelming sound. Animated with the most modern software and acoustically accompanied by the music of Luca 
                        Longobardi, a skilful multimedia show was created in which space and work merge. The result is projected onto the floor and walls of the large 
                        hall of the Kunstkraftwerk, creating a dynamic fresco of shapes and colors. The visitors do not stand in front of the works as in a museum, but 
                        rather stroll through the virtual Hundertwasser landscapes as protagonists, so to speak.</p>
                    <p><em>Like in any domain, it is always good to let yourself inspired by the masters...immerse yourself in their knowledge and experience and 
                        merge it with your own taste.</em></p>
                        <figure><picture><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemici/hundertwasserexperience.png" media="(max-width: 700px)"/><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemedii/hundertwasserexperience.png" media="(max-width: 1200px)"><img src="resurse/images/hundertwasserexperience.png" alt="Hundertwasser Experience" title="Hundertwasser Experience"/></picture><figcaption>Hundertwasser Experience, Leipzig</figcaption></figure>
                </section>
                <section id="southwesterndesertofjordan">
                    <h2>Southwestern Desert of Jordan</h2>
                    <!--<figure><picture><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemici/southwesterndesertofjordan.png" media="(max-width: 700px)"/><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemedii/southwesterndesertofjordan.png" media="(max-width: 1200px)"><img src="resurse/images/southwesterndesertofjordan.png" alt="Southwestern Desert of Jordan" title="Southwestern Desert of Jordan"/></picture><figcaption>The Petra Great Temple, Jordan</figcaption></figure>-->
                    <p>Probably one of my most beloved trips is when i had the oportunity to visit the Great Temple in Petra, Jordania. 
                        Petra is an ancient city with massive tombs and  temples carved directly into pink sandstone cliffs. 
                        <strong>This place is considered one of the Seven Wonders of the World.</strong> 
                        If you want to avoid the crowds, the best time to visit Jordan is in the off season. Bring water, snacks and cash. 
                        Another important thing to remember is to wear sunscreen and bring good walking shoes!</p>
                        <figure><picture><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemici/southwesterndesertofjordan.png" media="(max-width: 700px)"/><source srcset="resurse/images/pozemedii/southwesterndesertofjordan.png" media="(max-width: 1200px)"><img src="resurse/images/southwesterndesertofjordan.png" alt="Southwestern Desert of Jordan" title="Southwestern Desert of Jordan"/></picture><figcaption>The Petra Great Temple, Jordan</figcaption></figure>
